It's a major annoyance if you start using Stash using the documentation only to be reminded lateron that you have to start all over again.

Currently the really important information about using an external database is located deep down in "Administering Stash -> Advanced actions" [http://confluence.atlassian.com/display/STASH/Connecting+Stash+to+an+external+database]

{quote}
Stash does not currently support migration between database systems. If you would like to connect the application to an external database, you must do so *before starting Stash for the first time*. Doing otherwise will result in data loss.
{quote}

As there is currently no way to migrate between databases, please add this kind of information in the "Getting started" section (Installating Stash on Windows/Linux/Mac), together with a link to the appropriate page.

*Rating*: :( Bad

{panel:title=What do you like?|borderColor=#ccc| titleBGColor=#c2ffa2|bgColor=#fff}
Much of the standard functionality is the same on all Atlassian tools. That is a good thing!
{panel}

{panel:title=What needs to be improved?|borderColor=#ccc| titleBGColor=#faacad|bgColor=#fff}
I can't make an application link to locally installed confluence or jira. I got this error:

An error occurred when trying to create the application link in the remote application.
There is no application type 'stash' installed.
{panel}

*Rating*: :) Good

{panel:title=What do you like?|borderColor=#ccc| titleBGColor=#c2ffa2|bgColor=#fff}
The syntax highlighting on the browse pages is generally good, and the interface is way cleaner than the equivalent in Crucible.
{panel}

{panel:title=What needs to be improved?|borderColor=#ccc| titleBGColor=#faacad|bgColor=#fff}
Unfortunately, there are missing language heuristics in the syntax highlighting code (Markdown -> .md, etc), and I'm not sure the default is very helpful (Java? or something?). If the syntax highlighting does not recognize file's language properly (by extension or other heuristic), shouldn't it abandon highlighting entirely?
{panel}

*Reporter*: Daniel Stockman
*E-mail*: [mailto:daniels@zillow.com]

*Rating*: :) Good

{panel:title=What do you like?|borderColor=#ccc| titleBGColor=#c2ffa2|bgColor=#fff}
Clean design...
{panel}

{panel:title=What needs to be improved?|borderColor=#ccc| titleBGColor=#faacad|bgColor=#fff}
Can we add and make default the "menlo" font-family (12px or 14px) for those who have it (mac users)? It looks so much better than basic Courier.
{panel}

*Reporter*: Rich Manalang
*E-mail*: [mailto:rmanalang@atlassian.com]

*Rating*: :) Good

{panel:title=What needs to be improved?|borderColor=#ccc| titleBGColor=#faacad|bgColor=#fff}
Gravatar support is broken; the "d" parameter default image URL needs to be URL encoded.  Otherwise, it appears to always send the default image, never the gravatar.  For example, it currently is:

background-image: url('http://www.gravatar.com/avatar/ae51ed14b4c252a0f2e3edabb908f139.jpg?s=48&d=http://vd-bs-06:7990/s/en_US/20120327163217357/1/1.0/_/download/resources/com.atlassian.stash.stash-web-plugin:avatar/avatar/default-avatar-48.png');

It should be:

background-image: url('http://www.gravatar.com/avatar/ae51ed14b4c252a0f2e3edabb908f139.jpg?s=48&d=http%3A%2F%2Fvd-bs-06%3A7990%2Fs%2Fen_US%2F20120327163217357%2F1%2F1.0%2F_%2Fdownload%2Fresources%2Fcom.atlassian.stash.stash-web-plugin%3Aavatar%2Favatar%2Fdefault-avatar-48.png');
{panel}
